item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
Who we are

Our website address is: http:.

What personal data we collect and why we collect it

Comments

When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor’s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.

An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.

Media

If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.

Contact forms

Cookies

If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.

If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.

When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select "Remember Me", your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.

If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.

Embedded content from other websites

Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.

These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.

Analytics

Who we share your data with

How long we retain your data

If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.

For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.

What rights you have over your data

If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.

Where we send your data

Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.

Your contact information

Additional information

How we protect your data

What data breach procedures we have in place

What third parties we receive data from

What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data

Industry regulatory disclosure requirements

The Organization recommendation

Jillian Scott

Jillian Scott, Esq. is the managing partner of Markowitz  & Mellencamp, P.C., established in 1983. Jillian has been accredited by the American Bar Association. As a leading lawyer in the firm, Jillian uses her experience and personal relationships to get results for all M&M's clients. She is a talented and hard working attorney who never stops trying to bring another win for her clients. Facebook Twitter Google-plus Linkedin

Andrew michaels

Andrew holds a Certified Elder Law Attorney (CELA) degree, and has over 18 years of experience as a prosecutor in New York State. Andrew has personally handled quite a few high-profile cases, both as prosecutor as well as a defense lawyer. He has represented over 100 New York firms in various litigations, an has only lost once, throughout his entire career. It wasn't his fault, the guy was clearly guilty. Facebook Twitter Google-plus Linkedin

Robert Jeffries

Robert might look like a sweet old man, but when he puts on the famous litigation suit, he becomes a cunning lion. You really want a guy like Robert on your team. Finding loop holes and loose ends is what has made Robert famous in the New York district and beyond as one of the shrudest, most highly skilled lawyer in the business. Don't miss his closing arguments, they have never failed. Facebook Twitter Google-plus Linkedin

WALKID

Walking School Bus Volunteering Aid


Walkid wants to spread the message of hope and compassion.

We believe that a single action can make a difference in the community,
and that collective action can greatly impact the world

What is Walking school bus(WSB) program?

How to become a WSB volunteer?

Where are WSB councils?

How to work with children?



THE WALKING SCHOOL BUS PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School bus (WSB) Program is a pioneering way of walking primary school children to and from the school with volunteers along a safely audited route. It is a school bus powered by legs and not by an engine. School going kids walk to school in a group with Volunteers as Driver and Conductor. The bus stops at pre-determined stops to pick up children along the way from their home, and vice versa for the way to school. There are around 70 Councils in Victoria who have adopted the WSB program.

WSB Volunteer

WSB volunteers are adults who engage in the WSB Program to walk children to and from the school along with a predetermined safe route.

WSB Benefits

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. Children can get to school safely and on time.
2. Children get regular physical activity and exercise, gain a sense of independence.
3. It provides a safer, non-polluting, and sustainable transport alternative.
4. Reduces time pressure for parents as they dont have to accompany their children to school every day.
5. Reduces the number of vehicles subsequently eases traffic congestion around the school zones.

DID YOU KNOW

Only ONE in FOUR Australian children walk to school due to lack of adult supervision and safety concerns. Together we can make a difference. Create a safer school route by engaging in the Walking School Bus Program.

1 Number of schools engaged in the WSB Program 1 Number of volunteers in the WSB program 1 Number of council in the WSB Programs

We need more WSB Volunteers

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

Volunteering for a few hours can make a difference in society. Start your WSB volunteering journey today.

FIVE STEPS TO START YOUR WSB VOLUNTEERING JOURNEY

1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation
  • All Councils require volunteers a Police check and a Working with Childrens Check
3. Find your council based on your preferred location
  • Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.
4. Contact with the Council

  • You can contact the council for inquiries with your WSB volunteering journey.

5. Submit your WSB Volunteer Application
  • When you are ready with all the required documents and requirements, you can submit your application. Most councils use email for the application process.

FIND WSB COUNCILS NEAR YOU

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Input your preferred location on the Enter your location block.

Select Radius

Select the preferred radius (1 km to 300 km) to find the nearest councils within that radius based on your location.

Select the WSB council

Choose your preferred WSB council on the map

Direction

Click on Get Directions to get routes to the preferred council from your location.

Tips for WSB volunteers

MELBOURNE WSB PROGRAM

If you're having fun to help students to school safely Become a WSB Program's Volunteer

the walking school bus

WSB Program

A Walking School Bus is a school bus powered not by an engine but by legs. Children walk in a group to school, with an adult 'driver' in the front and an adult 'conductor' at the rear.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program have many benefits for children and school. If you want to know more click here

The WSB volunteer will help children go to school safety

MELBOURNE WSB PROGRAM

If you're having fun to help students to school safely Become a WSB Program's Volunteer

the walking school bus

WSB Program

A Walking School Bus is a school bus powered not by an engine but by legs. Children walk in a group to school, with an adult 'driver' in the front and an adult 'conductor' at the rear.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program have many benefits for children and school. If you want to know more click here

The WSB volunteer will help children go to school safety

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: user

WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Having fun to help students to school safely? Become a WSB Program's Volunteer!



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School Bus Program refer to the school, local council, and the volunteers of the WSB create a walking school bus which powered by legs, Volunteers like a driver to lead students group walking to school, and Volunteers as 'driver' in the front and rear. There is almost 70 local council engaged in the WSB Program in the VIC, AU.  Many buses have become a very positive part of school and community life. 

WSB Volunteer

The WSB volunteer indicates the adults who engage in the WSB Program. They may come from different industries or they own different cultures. They all focus to help students go to school safely.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. The WSB program help students get to school safely.
2. The students can learn knowledge about traffic safety.
3. The students can get more regular physical activities that benefit their health.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEER

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

This website aims to encourage people to engage in WSB Program and Provideinstruction for guiding people to be a volunteer.

Status of Volunteer

1 Accidents in School Zone

1 Existing Volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text.

1 Shortage of volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text.

FIVE STEPS TO BECOME A WSB VOLUNTEER

Most frequent questions and answers
1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation

All Councils require volunteers a Police Check. The volunteers who work with children need a Working with Childrens Check

3. Select a Council you prefer in our Council Recommendation

Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.

4. Contact with the Council

You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.

5. Submit your Application

When you prepare all the material and requirements from the council, You can submit you application. Most councils use email to receive the material. Here, you should note that you are interesting in WSB program

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

Our gallery

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Please input your address on the right location box.

Select Radius

Select the distance, which decide a recommendation arrange that centers on you

Select your prefer COUNCIL

Select an council you like on the right map

Derection

Click the get direction, this provide a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: User1
item.content:encoded:
WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Having fun to help students to school safely? Become a WSB Program's Volunteer!



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School Bus Program refer to the school, local council, and the volunteers of the WSB create a walking school bus which powered by legs, Volunteers like a driver to lead students group walking to school, and Volunteers as 'driver' in the front and rear. There is almost 70 local council engaged in the WSB Program in the VIC, AU.  Many buses have become a very positive part of school and community life. 

WSB Volunteer

The WSB volunteer indicates the adults who engage in the WSB Program. They may come from different industries or they own different cultures. They all focus to help students go to school safely.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. The WSB program help students get to school safely.
2. The students can learn knowledge about traffic safety.
3. The students can get more regular physical activities that benefit their health.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEER

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

This website aims to encourage people to engage in WSB Program and Provideinstruction for guiding people to be a volunteer.

Status of Volunteer

1 Accidents in School Zone

1 Existing Volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text.

1 Shortage of volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text.

FIVE STEPS TO BECOME A WSB VOLUNTEER

Most frequent questions and answers
1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation

All Councils require volunteers a Police Check. The volunteers who work with children need a Working with Childrens Check

3. Select a Council you prefer in our Council Recommendation

Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.

4. Contact with the Council

You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.

5. Submit your Application

When you prepare all the material and requirements from the council, You can submit you application. Most councils use email to receive the material. Here, you should note that you are interesting in WSB program

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

Our gallery

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Please input your address on the right location box.

Select Radius

Select the distance, which decide a recommendation arrange that centers on you

Select your prefer COUNCIL

Select an council you like on the right map

Derection

Click the get direction, this provide a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
WALKING SCHOOL BUS VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Get Started

What is the walking school bus program

Where you can engage walking school bus program

How to be a volunteer of walking school bus program

hOW DID YOU WORK WITH CHILD



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School bus (WSB) Program is a pioneering way of walking primary school children to and from the school with volunteers along a safely audited route. It is a school bus powered by legs and not by an engine. School going kids walk to school in a group with Volunteers as Driver and Conductor. The bus stops at pre-determined stops to pick up children along the way from their home, and vice versa for the way to school. There are around 70 Councils in Victoria who have adopted the WSB program.

WSB Volunteer

WSB volunteers are adults who engage in the WSB Program to walk children to and from the school along with a predetermined safe route.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. Children can get to school safely and on time.
2. Children get regular physical activity and exercise, gain a sense of independence.
3. It provides a safer, non-polluting, and sustainable transport alternative.
4. Reduces time pressure for parents as they dont have to accompany their children to school every day.
5. Reduces the number of vehicles subsequently eases traffic congestion around the school zones.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEERS

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

Volunteering for a few hours can make a difference in society. Start your WSB volunteering journey today

FIVE STEPS TO START YOUR WSB VOLUNTEERING JOURNEY

1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation
  • All Councils require volunteers a Police check and a Working with Childrens Check
3. IT Find your council based on your preferred location
  • Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.
4. Contact with the Council
  • You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.
5. Submit your WSB Volunteer Application
  • When you are ready with all the required documents and requirements from the council, you can submit with your volunteering application. Most councils use email for the application process.

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Input your preferred location on the Enter your location block.

Select Radius

Select the preferred radius (1 km to 300 km) to find the nearest councils within that radius based on your location.

COUNCIL SHOULD BE PREFERRED

Select an council you like on the right map

Direction

Click the get direction, this provides a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

How to work with kids?
